# Heterogeneous-TP proportional sharding — vLLM 0.22.69 source patch.
#
# Re-targeted from the zaya 0.22-therock tree to the combined image's vLLM 0.22.69
# (editable at /app/vllm). Apply with `patch -p1` from /app/vllm (the Dockerfile.combined
# WITH_HET_TP=1 step does this). Pairs with patches/het_tp.py, installed to
# /app/vllm/vllm/distributed/het_tp.py. Strict no-op unless VLLM_TP_CU_WEIGHTS is set.
#
# Splits ONLY the FFN/MoE *intermediate* (reduction) dimension proportional to per-rank
# CU counts (e.g. 64:56), so the bigger card stops spin-waiting at the all-reduce barrier.
# Attention heads + vocab/lm_head stay on the stock even path. See patches/HET_TP_PATCH.md.
#
# Files (3 — config.py is NOT touched: in 0.22.69 the MoE intermediate split + expert
# loaders moved out of fused_moe/config.py into fused_moe/layer.py):
#   vllm/model_executor/layers/linear.py      Column/Merged/Row sizing + v2-param stamp
#   vllm/model_executor/parameter.py          load_{column,merged_column,row}_weight offset
#   vllm/model_executor/layers/fused_moe/layer.py
#                                             MoE intermediate split, _het_moe_shard,
#                                             _load_w13/_load_w2 offset, combined-w13 guard
#
